{center}
{subhead}Amiga Expo Announces New Exhibitors and More{def}
{left}
{pp}
14.1.2002
{pp}
It's an exciting new year for Amiga Expo as we've begun 2002 by
signing up a brand new bunch of exhibitors and speakers for the show.
{pp}
{bold}Exhibitors{nobold}
{pp}
-MAME (Multi Arcade Machine Emulator) developer Arcade-in-a-Box will
be exhibiting their all-in-one solution for creating a fantastic home{p}
-arcade experience.{p}
-Video Hardware will be exhibiting and demoing
Newtek's Video Toaster[2] and the latest Lightwave as well.{p}
-Extreme Corporation will be showing Amiga Extreme - their new AmigaOS
XL{p}
-Amiga solution.{p}
-Ideas2Reality will be showing the Reality Station and
their line of Amiga, PPC and x86 solutions.{p}
-FWD Computing will have their line of CDROMS for Amiga, Linux and Windows for sale at the
show.
{pp}
{bold}Speakers{nobold}
{pp}
We'll have speakers showing MAME products, video editing solutions,
Amiga advancements, classic computer and game celebrities and much
more.
{pp}
{bold}Banquet{nobold}
{pp}
We plan to host a celebrity panel at our banquet discussing the
future of computing across many platforms. Be served wonderful food
in a festive atmosphere amongst your fellow enthusiasts and hear
about what's to come!
{pp}
{bold}Free Exhibit Space{nobold}
{pp}
There is also a limited amount of space available, at no charge, to
anyone interested in exhibiting their MAME or arcade game cabinets at
the show. People interested in exhibiting classic computers and
console game machines are also invited to take advantage of this free
display space. You must contact us soon if you'd like to participate.
{pp}
Visit our web site and order your tickets online or by phone or mail.
You best hurry as advance purchase discounts will be ending soon, the
discount rooms at the hotel are filling up and the banquet has
LIMITED seating that is selling out fast!
{pp}